id: pm-4bzq
title: "GH-472: create error for missing required custom fields lists the field names"
description: "Dogfood GH-472: creating an item whose type has required custom fields fails without naming the missing fields, costing agents a pm schema round-trip. Duplicate check: searched create required fields error — pm-qmjx (GH-441) covers the create --help required-list mislabeling; this is the runtime error path, related but distinct."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 2
tags[5]: agent-experience,"area:cli",errors,gh-issue,schema
created_at: "2026-07-06T21:09:17.588Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-08T17:09:39.905Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: pm create failure for missing required type-specific fields names each missing field (and expected type/format) in the error and recovery examples; consistent across strict and progressive create-mode; covered by specs
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: high
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-qmjx,related,"2026-07-06T21:09:53.786Z",null,null
body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/472\n\nWhen `pm create` rejects an item because the type has required custom fields, include the required field names (and expected types) in the structured error instead of a generic message, saving agents a `pm schema` round-trip.\n\nRelated: pm-qmjx (GH-441 type-aware create help mislabels required flags) — same required-fields metadata source should power both help and error paths."
